```mermaid
flowchart TD
  subgraph Client
    U[Player UI]
    FUI[Frontend UI: Create or Join Room]
    U --> FUI
    FUI --> S1[Socket emit join_room]
    S1 --> BE_handle_join[Backend handle_join_room]
  end

  subgraph Backend
    BE_handle_join --> RedisGet[Redis GET room state]
    RedisGet --> CheckExisting{Room exists}
    CheckExisting -->|No| CreateState[create initial state]
    CheckExisting -->|Yes| LoadState[load saved state]
    CreateState --> RedisSet[Redis SET room state]
    LoadState --> RedisSet
    RedisSet --> EmitAssigned[emit assigned_role to caller]
  end

  EmitAssigned --> ClientReceiveAssigned[Frontend receives assigned_role payload]
  ClientReceiveAssigned --> RenderBoard[renderBoard with myRole]

  %% Move lifecycle
  U --> ClickSelect[User clicks square or selects piece]
  ClickSelect --> EmitPropose[Socket emit propose_move with from and to]
  EmitPropose --> BE_propose_move[Backend handle_propose_move]
  BE_propose_move --> FetchState[Redis GET room state]
  FetchState --> Validate[Call is_legal_move]
  Validate -->|Illegal| EmitRejected[emit move_rejected to caller]
  EmitRejected --> ClientShowRejected[Frontend shows rejection message]
  Validate -->|Legal| ApplyMove[Mutate board and update castling and turn]
  ApplyMove --> SaveState[Redis SET room state]
  SaveState --> EmitMoveExec[emit move_executed to room channel]
  EmitMoveExec --> ClientsUpdate[Clients receive move_executed and render]

  %% Spectator note
  ClientsUpdate -->|all connected in room| Spectators[Spectators and players]
  RenderBoard -->|local UI update| ClientsUpdate
```
